author: @SPLICY
text: This video is ON POINT!  It's surprising how many data scientists I've met that are not curious about the data.  More than the investigations Josh suggests, I highly recommend looking at data on the most granular level.  Seeing data at its most fundamental level can give you insights or ideas that may not be apparent when doing global analysis.  Additionally, visualize the data when you can!  It's difficult to understate how much visualizations have helped me over the years.  Finally, akin to the demographics Josh was talking about in his first example, try slicing the data in different ways.  Does it change by day? What do the outliers look like? etc.  Remember:  BE CURIOUS
